### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@token = Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@doctorId = 1

### 1. Criar novo médico
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "userId": 1,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. João Silva",
  "cpf": "12345678901",
  "crm": "12345-SP",
  "specialty": "Cardiologia",
  "phone": "11987654321"
}

### 2. Listar todos os médicos (paginado)
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors?page=0&size=10&sort=fullName,asc
Authorization: {{token}}

### 3. Buscar médico por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}
Authorization: {{token}}

### 4. Buscar médico inexistente (deve retornar 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/999
Authorization: {{token}}

### 5. Atualizar médico
PUT {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "userId": 1,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. João Silva Oliveira",
  "cpf": "12345678901",
  "crm": "12345-SP",
  "specialty": "Cardiologia Intervencionista",
  "phone": "11987654321"
}

### 6. Excluir médico
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/doctors/{{doctorId}}
Authorization: {{token}}

### 7. Buscar médico por nome
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/search/name?name=João&page=0&size=10
Authorization: {{token}}

### 8. Buscar médico por CRM
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/search/crm?crm=12345-SP
Authorization: {{token}}

### 9. Buscar médicos por especialidade
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/search/specialty?specialty=Cardiologia&page=0&size=10
Authorization: {{token}}

### 10. Filtrar médicos (múltiplos critérios)
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/filter?hospitalId=1&specialty=Cardiologia&name=João&page=0&size=10&sort=fullName,asc
Authorization: {{token}}

### 11. Filtrar por hospital
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/filter?hospitalId=1&page=0&size=10
Authorization: {{token}}

### 12. Filtrar por especialidade
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors/filter?specialty=Cardiologia&page=0&size=10
Authorization: {{token}}

### 13. Listar com múltiplas ordenações
GET {{baseUrl}}/doctors?page=0&size=10&sort=specialty,asc&sort=fullName,asc
Authorization: {{token}}

### 14. Criar médico com validação inválida (CPF curto)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "userId": 1,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. Maria Santos",
  "cpf": "123",
  "crm": "67890-RJ",
  "specialty": "Pediatria",
  "phone": "11999999999"
}

### 15. Criar médico com user inexistente (deve retornar 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "userId": 999,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. Pedro Costa",
  "cpf": "98765432100",
  "crm": "11111-MG",
  "specialty": "Ortopedia",
  "phone": "11988888888"
}

### 16. Criar médico com hospital inexistente (deve retornar 404)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "userId": 1,
  "hospitalId": 999,
  "fullName": "Dra. Ana Paula",
  "cpf": "11111111111",
  "crm": "22222-RS",
  "specialty": "Dermatologia",
  "phone": "11977777777"
}

### 17. Criar médico com CRM duplicado (deve retornar erro)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "userId": 2,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. Carlos Souza",
  "cpf": "22222222222",
  "crm": "12345-SP",
  "specialty": "Neurologia",
  "phone": "11966666666"
}

### 18. Criar médico com CPF duplicado (deve retornar erro)
POST {{baseUrl}}/doctors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "userId": 2,
  "hospitalId": 1,
  "fullName": "Dr. Lucas Mendes",
  "cpf": "12345678901",
  "crm": "99999-SP",
  "specialty": "Psiquiatria",
  "phone": "11955555555"
}
